Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.82,0:00:58.38,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(600,560)\pos(315,170)}16~The Cursed Fountain
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.01,0:01:52.97,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Thirsty... So thirsty...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.64,0:02:14.54,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Could someone explain to me why we always end up in such situations?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.15,0:02:17.77,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Because we spend our time taking tours and detours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.77,0:02:21.34,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,When we're not busy being tourists, we're saving the weak and the helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.34,0:02:25.26,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but we're heroes. And a hero has a duty to help others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.63,0:02:29.01,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm with Grovy, a hero is there to make the world a nicer place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.35,0:02:33.60,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,I agree as well. But there are tragic stories and people to save on every street corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.60,0:02:36.52,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,We have to know what we want, what's our priority?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.00,0:02:42.64,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know... I don't know anymore... My brain is fried.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.64,0:02:44.02,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Yugo, answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.20,0:02:47.03,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Our priority?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.03,0:02:49.70,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Well, to find Shinonome's Dofus.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.70,0:02:51.15,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Well it doesn't look like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.15,0:02:54.60,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,It's been weeks since we left, and we're not even halfway there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.60,0:02:56.47,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, it's going to take months.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.47,0:02:58.26,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Have you thought about Adamaï?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.62,0:03:02.98,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,You promised him that we'd be back as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.73,0:03:06.86,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Each one of us has put their heart into your quest, Yugo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.26,0:03:10.06,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,So if you wish to fight the world's misery, so be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.06,0:03:13.82,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,But if you don't mind, we'll do that after we're done with this mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.32,0:03:15.43,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,I-I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.05,0:03:20.99,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,I understand, Eva. From now on, we'll focus on our quest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.07,0:03:45.45,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Look over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:47.46,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,It's the oasis that the map mentioned!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.87,0:03:49.66,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.10,0:03:53.65,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Over there! I can hear running water!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.65,0:03:54.87,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, over there, there's an entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.59,0:03:57.98,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wait for me guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.84,0:04:12.83,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,That's it, we're dead. This is paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.87,0:04:22.86,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Grovy, it hurts me to admit it, but you've summed it all up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.54,0:04:26.78,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Water!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.78,0:04:37.51,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Get back, strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.51,0:04:41.07,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Bordegann, and I won't let anybody drink this fountain's water.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.07,0:04:42.04,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.04,0:04:43.26,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,And why can't we drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.45,0:04:53.21,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Have pity my lord, we are in dire need of refreshment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.51,0:04:55.64,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that it's rather hot in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.64,0:04:58.38,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sorry, you can't drink this water.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.78,0:05:01.97,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think I'll drink to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.85,0:05:09.60,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me sir, but why can't we drink from it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.95,0:05:12.65,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you drink from it? Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.65,0:05:13.83,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.53,0:05:15.98,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,because you must not drink from it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.98,0:05:18.98,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! That's a pretty short argument you have there, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.20,0:05:22.62,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! I'm with my buddy Ruel on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.25,0:05:26.86,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.13,0:05:28.54,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.53,0:05:33.83,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, I beg of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.65,0:05:37.96,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive him, he's not a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:40.94,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that... he doesn't know what he's doing anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.43,0:05:43.34,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,I have some water.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.71,0:05:46.87,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Here, drink it all if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.87,0:05:48.50,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, thanks, Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.21,0:05:52.20,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Women and children first!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.78,0:05:57.70,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Get back, stranger. My name is Bordegann and I protect--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.70,0:06:00.78,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Bordegann, I know. I'm not interested in the fountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.78,0:06:03.24,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just bringing you something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.24,0:06:04.37,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.80,0:06:08.42,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,How thoughtful. Thanks, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.10,0:06:17.71,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Today I have some dried fruits, cereals, and for dessert: a calouga.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.33,0:06:22.94,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, how nice, that's my favorite dessert. How did you guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.81,0:06:26.45,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Because I come here every day, Bordegann.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.45,0:06:29.60,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Really? And... and what's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.60,0:06:30.60,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Alia...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.26,0:06:33.10,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Alia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.10,0:06:36.04,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Alia? That's a pretty name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.04,0:06:37.90,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Well, thanks a lot, Alia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.31,0:06:54.26,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,See you tomorrow, Bordegann...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.14,0:07:02.82,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd please follow me,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.82,0:07:06.76,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,my village isn't far from here. Allow me to offer you a bit of hospitality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.10,0:07:29.86,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,The village's fountain is... right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.48,0:07:40.56,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,We don't see many strangers around here. Stay a while, I'd be glad to get news from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.56,0:07:43.86,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,It would be a pleasure, but we still have a long journey ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.86,0:07:45.55,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better not linger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.55,0:07:49.15,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,At least take a bit of food, the road to the south coast is tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.15,0:07:52.69,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,In order to cross this desert, you'll need sufficient provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.69,0:07:55.14,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! That's very kind of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.14,0:07:58.46,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Amy, I'm going with Yugo. Go get the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.94,0:07:59.90,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,We'll meet here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.64,0:08:14.38,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You're not supposed to hit old people!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:18.59,Default,Orphan Iop,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Bordegann, I guard this fountain, and you won't get near it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.96,0:08:25.58,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Listen kiddo. I pity you, so I'll spare you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.75,0:08:28.74,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,You're really asking for that spanking!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.55,0:08:37.66,Default,Mama Pandawa,0000,0000,0000,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:41.38,Default,Mama Pandawa,0000,0000,0000,,Just stop already!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.79,0:08:44.30,Default,Mama Pandawa,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive him, strangers, he has no manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.30,0:08:48.70,Default,Mama Pandawa,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to eat or drink, there's Louca's Inn. I was just going there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.70,0:08:51.06,Default,Mama Pandawa,0000,0000,0000,,Get back home right now, before I get angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.06,0:08:54.19,Default,Mama Pandawa,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of manners are those?! Now, off with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:58.00,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,I think we've stumbled upon a village of lunatics.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.77,0:09:07.28,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,I'll also add a bit of dried meat, as a side dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.28,0:09:10.58,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Why is Bordegann guarding the fountain? What's so special about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.79,0:09:14.50,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,It's cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.35,0:09:18.90,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Cursed?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.35,0:09:22.89,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,It's a long and sad story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.89,0:09:24.38,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Bordegann is my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.38,0:09:29.03,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,We all came from another island that was engulfed by the rise of waters from Ogrest's Chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.03,0:09:31.86,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Bordegann had heard of an abandoned village.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.86,0:09:34.34,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Conditions would be harsh, the place would be isolated from everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.34,0:09:37.50,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,but what mattered most was that we would have a new home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.91,0:09:43.84,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Bordegann was the one leading the first expedition tasked with locating the place and restoring the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.84,0:09:47.45,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,But after two weeks without any news, we decided to go looking for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.60,0:09:52.59,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,The inhabitants had all disappeared, and Bordegann was the only one left...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.59,0:09:54.58,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,There, near that cursed fountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.65,0:10:10.36,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,He had gone half crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.40,0:10:14.84,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,He had lost his memory and didn't recognize me anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.84,0:10:18.12,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what happened, but I refuse to believe that it's my love's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.12,0:10:22.62,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,The fountain's the one to blame. Bordegann is just trying to protect us from it, I'm certain of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.69,0:10:28.63,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since, I've been taking care of him, I bring him food every day, hoping he'll recover his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.63,0:10:32.61,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,The villagers think that I'm crazy, that there's no hope, but I'll wait as long as needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.48,0:10:36.22,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,I... I can't abandon him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.02,0:10:43.20,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,There {\i1}must{\i0} be a way to restore his mind... We'll help you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.20,0:10:44.71,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Yugo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.53,0:10:46.85,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Eva.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.85,0:10:47.94,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.94,0:10:51.86,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry Alia. We have an urgent quest to carry out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.86,0:10:54.15,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll come back to help you, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.15,0:10:55.21,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Won't we, Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.66,0:11:09.21,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Alia's very pretty, but she's kind of bird-brained, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.21,0:11:12.18,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,As for me, such a boor as Bordegann wouldn't be enough to keep me around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.18,0:11:15.61,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,I would've run off long ago to see if the grass was greener elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.61,0:11:18.10,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,What were they thinking, burrowing in such a godforsaken place?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.10,0:11:20.30,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Even their kids have gone nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.30,0:11:23.56,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I do understand her. Love can sometimes turn you completely Iop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.56,0:11:24.75,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.83,0:11:31.15,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,No, I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:35.75,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,What? You can't walk? Do you want me to carry you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:39.50,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,No, I can't... I don't want to leave them like that. We've got to go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.50,0:11:40.82,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,What's she talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.82,0:11:44.37,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Go back? But why? Did you forget something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.58,0:11:50.85,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Eva.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:12:00.83,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Can someone explain to me what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.20,0:12:08.36,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you have done some research...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.36,0:12:11.50,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but we didn't find anything. Only Bordegann is left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.50,0:12:14.60,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,The villagers that accompanied him disappeared without a trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.60,0:12:17.18,Default,Louca,0000,0000,0000,,That cursed fountain's the one to blame, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.18,0:12:21.46,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,But as I told you, we don't know if it's the water or the place that's cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.46,0:12:25.34,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Well then we're going to study it stone by stone, there's bound to be a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.34,0:12:27.20,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of clue are we looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.20,0:12:32.33,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Anything that looks magical. A gemstone, runes, a stele.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.33,0:12:34.06,Default,Client 1,0000,0000,0000,,You're forgetting something...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.60,0:12:35.88,Default,Client 1,0000,0000,0000,,Bordegann.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.88,0:12:37.95,Default,Client 1,0000,0000,0000,,He won't let you get near the fountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.95,0:12:41.50,Default,Client 2,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We've already tried several times, we never succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.50,0:12:44.78,Default,Louca,0000,0000,0000,,They're right. Bordegann is too strong. It's a lost cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.78,0:12:48.56,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Well it just so happens that we're specialists in lost causes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.56,0:12:51.39,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's even how you recognize heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.52,0:12:58.18,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Get back, stranger! My name is Bordegann and I protect--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.18,0:13:02.90,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Bordegann, I know, I'm not interested in the fountain, I'm just bringing you something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.90,0:13:03.94,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.61,0:13:07.84,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,...and your favorite dessert: a calouga.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.55,0:13:09.81,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,A calouga!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.81,0:13:10.92,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.92,0:13:12.76,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Ready to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.76,0:13:17.86,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Grovy! The point is not to fight him, but to immobilize him and find some clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.86,0:13:19.50,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on, I was just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.50,0:13:20.40,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.38,0:13:25.41,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.41,0:13:26.37,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,What in the...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.37,0:13:27.86,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Your turn, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.47,0:13:32.58,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,We've got to check every nook and cranny.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:33.66,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.66,0:13:34.62,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,What in the...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.62,0:13:36.44,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry, Bordegann.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:43.99,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,No! The fountain! You must not get near it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.86,0:13:58.54,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Villains! You will taste my wrath!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.86,0:14:19.09,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,He's a tough one, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.09,0:14:22.71,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Eva. Couldn't I use my sword? Just a little bit, to see if...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:24.08,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Grovy, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.08,0:14:27.04,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Well, at least tomorrow he'll have forgotten everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:29.14,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we'll try something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.14,0:14:30.39,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.00,0:14:33.14,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, {\i1}our{\i0} marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.14,0:14:35.51,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, hurry up, the mayor is waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.51,0:14:37.74,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, miss! Err... Alia!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.74,0:14:39.70,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,One moment, I'm going to find my spear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.99,0:14:48.97,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, haven't I forgotten something? Now what was it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.97,0:14:51.80,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Bordegann! We're going to be late!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.80,0:14:53.15,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.94,0:14:57.30,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Get back, stranger, nobody must get near this fountain!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:02.58,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Grovy, what was your plan again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.80,0:15:11.74,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! A calouga!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.48,0:15:22.14,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,This is how my master got me out of a well that I had hidden in to sulk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.27,0:15:26.14,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,He's biting! He's biting, come help!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.81,0:15:30.50,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,It's a big one, a real big one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.76,0:15:32.11,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,All together!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.05,0:15:40.01,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Yugo, what was your idea again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:44.70,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,...and your favorite dessert: a calouga!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.70,0:15:48.13,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,My favorite? Really? But... but how do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.70,0:15:52.99,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Oh it's a very long story, but I can tell you about it, if you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.45,0:15:57.02,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,With pleasure, stranger. I love stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.02,0:15:59.22,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,At least... I-I think I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:01.96,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,Ruel can talk for whole days without stopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.32,0:16:04.90,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,A treasure like you've never seen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.90,0:16:09.86,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Kamas by the hundreds, by the thousands! Ha, I believed I was in Enutrof's heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.86,0:16:14.38,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Alas, yeah, alas...\N...managed to steal from me. Such boldness!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.38,0:16:17.86,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Luckily, they were lead by a boss as ugly and stupid as my great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.86,0:16:19.65,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,I say luckily, because, this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.65,0:16:23.26,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,I had skimped a bit on the costs, and my steed wasn't of the highest grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.26,0:16:28.26,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, had it been a matter of speed...\N...So I said to him: "Do you take me for a bank or what?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.26,0:16:30.98,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,"This shovel isn't even worth the earth that soils it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.98,0:16:35.62,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,"You think you can scam me, kiddo, but I wouldn't put Kamas on it."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.62,0:16:41.82,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,With a man of my rank... it was a bold move. And in such cases, there's only one solution: you don't let go of anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.82,0:16:47.10,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,I look him straight in the eyes and I say to him: "See, in this world there's two kinds of people, my friend:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.10,0:16:50.10,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,those who pay, and those who get paid!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.10,0:16:51.42,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.63,0:17:01.09,Default,Ruel,0000,0000,0000,,"You pay!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.78,0:17:05.05,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,Hands off my Eva!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.65,0:17:11.38,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you? What are you doing in my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.64,0:17:16.38,Default,Client 2,0000,0000,0000,,We told you so: not gonna work. We've already tried everything to get him out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.22,0:17:24.79,Default,Client 1,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... Hope is just an illusion. And we stopped having illusions long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.39,0:17:27.98,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what are these critters?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:31.17,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know. They were here when we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.17,0:17:34.22,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,If they could talk, they could tell us what really happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.08,0:17:36.40,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,They're really funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.60,0:17:37.89,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.89,0:17:40.57,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Without them, I think I would've lost all hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.56,0:17:45.12,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,You're right! There's always hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.12,0:17:48.31,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,We'll start over again from the beginning. Here's what we're gonna do...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.68,0:17:51.60,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name, stranger?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.60,0:17:53.25,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Alia, my name is--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.25,0:17:55.95,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Help! Somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.95,0:17:59.42,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! Someone's being attacked! Quick! Let's go check!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.17,0:18:06.47,Default,Amalia,0000,0000,0000,,Help! Somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.55,0:18:16.54,Default,Yugo,0000,0000,0000,,I'll handle him. Take care of the fountain!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.28,0:18:39.50,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Bubulle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.50,0:18:42.10,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,That's Bubulle, one of the villagers that disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.10,0:18:45.35,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What happened? Did anyone see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.42,0:18:57.24,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,The gemstones, at the bottom of the fountain, take them all out of the water, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.50,0:19:07.34,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,It's working!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.34,0:19:15.50,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,I've... understood... your... intentions... it's... the fountain... you're after!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.24,0:20:17.91,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,No, you must not get near the fountain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.09,0:20:25.99,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.85,0:20:33.06,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,The water serpent, I remember it. We're doomed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.48,0:20:43.03,Default,Alia,0000,0000,0000,,Bordegann, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.86,0:20:52.42,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Yugo!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.42,0:20:56.79,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,You have to strike the fountain! Now! With full power!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.14,0:21:46.43,Default,Client 1,0000,0000,0000,,It's too beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.70,0:21:56.56,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.56,0:21:59.05,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if I was asleep all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.05,0:22:01.82,Default,Bordegann,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't know how to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.48,0:22:04.41,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing you two reunited is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.41,0:22:06.62,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,You reminded me of what it means to be a "hero".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.62,0:22:08.98,Default,Tristepin,0000,0000,0000,,You know you're pretty nice as a zeroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.35,0:22:11.97,Default,Evangelyne,0000,0000,0000,,Heroes are there to make the world a nicer place, aren't they?
